1
00:00:05,288 --> 00:00:09,486
That the Ultimate Reality
is beautiful,

2
00:00:10,060 --> 00:00:14,596
is reassuring, encouraging, 
exciting …

3
00:00:14,596 --> 00:00:17,113
I can’t think of the actual word
that I’m looking for.

4
00:00:17,273 --> 00:00:20,446
[The Door to Theistic Culture]

5
00:00:20,656 --> 00:00:24,840
Because we are accustomed
to hear of reality

6
00:00:24,840 --> 00:00:26,985
and the Ultimate Reality,
and things like that,

7
00:00:26,985 --> 00:00:34,935
and the scientists have tried
to make that their …

8
00:00:34,935 --> 00:00:36,883
Everyone else’s dealing 
in interpretation—

9
00:00:36,883 --> 00:00:40,038
they’re dealing 
in hard facts about things.

10
00:00:40,558 --> 00:00:44,328
That the Ultimate Reality
is beautiful,

11
00:00:44,738 --> 00:00:46,088
they could say,

12
00:00:46,088 --> 00:00:49,178
“Yes, in its expression
or what we observe of it.”

13
00:00:49,178 --> 00:00:51,394
There are what they called 
‘the Elegant Universe’—

14
00:00:51,394 --> 00:00:54,020
those kind of things.
But that’s not good,

15
00:00:54,020 --> 00:00:58,300
that’s the least aspect 
of its beauty.

16
00:01:00,150 --> 00:01:05,770
That it can be beautiful the way 
a person can be beautiful,

17
00:01:05,770 --> 00:01:11,697
that their brains
cannot accommodate or digest.

18
00:01:11,697 --> 00:01:13,701
The beauty of a look,

19
00:01:13,701 --> 00:01:18,941
the beauty of emotional expression,

20
00:01:20,121 --> 00:01:23,461
those things
cannot be denied.

21
00:01:25,249 --> 00:01:29,221
The simple things 
that we can do in this world

22
00:01:29,221 --> 00:01:35,323
to deny that the Supreme Reality, 
the Supreme Absolute Truth

23
00:01:35,323 --> 00:01:39,483
can express such things,

24
00:01:39,483 --> 00:01:44,103
is sad and pathetic.

25
00:01:44,103 --> 00:01:48,395
That’s why when I was 
on my flight from Beijing to New York,

26
00:01:48,395 --> 00:01:55,155
and sitting next to me
is a computer scientist [who] teaches

27
00:01:55,315 --> 00:02:00,442
postdoctoral computer science
to very advanced people, and I thought,

28
00:02:00,442 --> 00:02:05,944
“Oh, this is an opportunity 
to ask a series of questions.”

29
00:02:05,944 --> 00:02:09,390
But I only needed to ask 
one question,

30
00:02:09,390 --> 00:02:12,130
which was,
and he agreed like,
 

31
00:02:12,130 --> 00:02:15,570
“Yes, ask me 
any question you like.”

32
00:02:15,570 --> 00:02:16,875
So I said,
 

33
00:02:18,155 --> 00:02:21,545
“As a hardcore 
computer scientist,

34
00:02:21,545 --> 00:02:24,545
the way you’ve been trained, 
the way you teach …

35
00:02:24,835 --> 00:02:29,015
Can you say
with absolute certainty,

36
00:02:29,725 --> 00:02:36,025
that the Original Source
of all aroma or fragrance

37
00:02:36,025 --> 00:02:41,757
has no olfactory capacity,
in other words, cannot smell?”

38
00:02:41,757 --> 00:02:43,027
And he said,

39
00:02:43,650 --> 00:02:47,000
“As you have worded this,

40
00:02:47,010 --> 00:02:49,850
no, I cannot say 
that with absolute certainty,

41
00:02:49,850 --> 00:02:54,535
I cannot deny
that prospect or possibility.”

42
00:02:54,535 --> 00:02:56,972
I said, 
“That’s all I need to know

43
00:02:56,972 --> 00:02:59,542
because now
you’ve opened the door

44
00:02:59,542 --> 00:03:02,401
for the possibility 
of theistic culture

45
00:03:02,401 --> 00:03:08,211
and the concept
of the Personality of Godhead,

46
00:03:08,211 --> 00:03:11,575
because we can make 
a similar case for each sense:

47
00:03:11,575 --> 00:03:13,871
can you say
with absolute certainty

48
00:03:13,871 --> 00:03:15,761
that the Original Source
 

49
00:03:15,761 --> 00:03:19,241
of all things to be seen

50
00:03:19,241 --> 00:03:22,166
has no seeing capacity?

51
00:03:22,166 --> 00:03:25,156
Seeing, smelling, hearing, 
tasting, touching, etc.

